quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  29,64,"And in no way is this present life (Literally: this lowly life, i.e., the life of this world) anything except a diversion and a plaything; and surely the Last Home is indeed the (Eternal) Life, (Literally: the all-blessed life) if they know (the Truth)"
  29,65,"So when they embark in the ships, they invoke Allah, making the religion His faithfully; then, as soon as He delivers them safe on the dry land, only then do they associate others (with Him)"
  29,66,"Let them disbelieve in whatever We brought them, and let them take their enjoyment; then they will eventually know"
  29,67,"And have they not seen that We have made a sanctuary secure, and mankind are snatched away all round about them? Do they then believe in untruth and disbelieve in the favor of Allah"
  29,68,"And who is more unjust than he who fabricates against Allah a lie, or cries lies to the Truth as soon as it comes to him? Is there not in Hell a lodging for the disbelievers"
  29,69,"And the ones who have striven in (our way), (Literally: in us) indeed We will definitely guide them to Our ways; and surely Allah is indeed with the fair-doers"
  30,1,"Alif, Lam, Mim (These are the names of letters of the Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows their meaning here)"
  30,2,The Romans have been overcome (by the Persians)
  30,3,"In the more adjacent (i.e., more easy to reach; the Levant) (part) of the earth. And even after their being overcome, they will overcome (the others)"
  30,4,"Within several years. To Allah belongs the Command ever before and ever after, and upon that day the believers will exult"
  30,5,"In the victory of Allah. He vindicates whomever He decides, and He is The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"